\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Real-data validation.} (a) CNN on CIFAR-10: Frobenius change versus linear probe $\Delta R^2$ (5 widths, 5 seeds). The CKA blind spot ($0.991$ CKA with $43\%$ Frobenius) persists for deeper architectures on real images. (b) FashionMNIST binary: kernel change versus $\Delta $Error. Larger kernel changes associate with \emph  {less} improvement ($\rho =-0.43$).}}{14}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
